♪ I'LL BE READY

01:41.101 --> 01:43.929
♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS

01:44.060 --> 01:47.107
♪ I'M ALWAYS HERE.

02:01.164 --> 02:04.124
[UPBEAT MUSIC]

02:57.220 --> 02:59.004
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

03:00.005 --> 03:03.270
[TRANQUIL MUSIC]

03:27.598 --> 03:29.121
-WHOO!

03:29.252 --> 03:31.036
-HEY, YOU ALREADY FOR
THE BIG RACE TOMORROW?

03:31.167 --> 03:32.560
-OH, YEAH. YOU GONNA RIDE?

03:32.690 --> 03:34.083
-NAH, MY KNEE'S ALL BANGED UP.

03:34.214 --> 03:35.954
-CODY: YEAH, WE'LL
MISS YOU OUT THERE.

03:36.085 --> 03:37.695
-HEY, WELL, LOOK AT IT THIS
WAY, AT LEAST YOU'VE GOT SOME

03:37.826 --> 03:39.697
-CHANCE OF WINNING TOMORROW.
-[LAUGHING]

03:39.828 --> 03:42.265
-EXCUSE ME, DO YOU KNOW WHERE
I CAN FIND CAROLINE HOLDEN?

03:42.396 --> 03:45.137
-YEAH, SHE'S WORKING
TOWER 14, JUST DOWN THE RAMP,

03:45.268 --> 03:47.227
TURN LEFT, YOU CAN'T MISS IT.

03:47.357 --> 03:48.358
-THANK YOU.
-NO PROBLEM.

03:52.014 --> 03:53.494
-WONDER WHAT THEY
WANT WITH CAROLINE.

03:53.624 --> 03:55.191
-NEWMIE: I DON'T KNOW.

03:55.322 --> 03:57.193
-WELL, I'LL SEE YOU NEWMIE.
-NEWMIE: ALL RIGHT.

04:09.466 --> 04:11.816
-HEY, WATCH IT.
-MAN: SORRY.

04:11.947 --> 04:13.514
-IT'S IN MY BRIEFCASE.

04:16.690 --> 04:18.387
-HI, CAN I HELP YOU?

04:19.128 --> 04:20.521
-ARE YOU CAROLINE HOLDEN?

04:20.651 --> 04:22.043
-YES.

04:22.784 --> 04:24.786
-THIS IS FOR YOU.
-CAROLINE: WHAT IS IT?

04:24.916 --> 04:26.962
-A SUMMONS FOR YOU TO
APPEAR IN CIVIL COURT.

04:27.092 --> 04:29.878
-CIVIL COURT? WHAT'S
THIS ALL ABOUT?

04:30.008 --> 04:32.141
-YOU'RE BEING SUED FOR
NEGLIGENCE IN THE DEATH

04:32.272 --> 04:33.751
OF THOMAS O'HARA.

04:34.448 --> 04:37.668
-THOMAS O'HARA? I'M
SORRY, I DON'T KNOW ANYBODY

04:37.799 --> 04:39.931
BY THAT NAME, YOU MIGHT
HAVE THE WRONG PERSON.

04:40.541 --> 04:41.977
-YOU DON'T REMEMBER HIM?

04:43.021 --> 04:44.284
HOW COULD YOU FORGET?

04:45.197 --> 04:48.679
-ELLEN: YOU MIGHT REMEMBER
HIM BETTER AS COWBOY?

04:48.810 --> 04:51.421
-HE'S MY SON, MY ONLY CHILD,

04:51.552 --> 04:52.988
AND YOU LEFT HIM TO DIE

04:53.118 --> 04:55.338
AT THE BOTTOM OF THE OCEAN.

04:56.078 --> 04:58.298
THEY STILL ALLOW YOU
TO BE A LIFEGUARD.

04:59.864 --> 05:01.257
-ROSE, LET'S GO.

05:01.779 --> 05:05.740
[MELANCHOLY MUSIC]

05:20.842 --> 05:22.931
-HEY, MILTON.
-HEY, MITCH.

05:23.758 --> 05:25.063
-HEY, YOU, WHERE YOU BEEN?

05:25.194 --> 05:26.151
I'VE BEEN LOOKING
ALL OVER FOR YOU.

05:26.282 --> 05:27.022
-THE COUNTY COUNCIL'S OFFICE.

05:27.152 --> 05:28.632
-WHAT'S UP?

05:28.763 --> 05:30.330
-THE COUNTY'S BEING SUED
FOR WRONGFUL DEATH

05:30.460 --> 05:31.809
BY THE FAMILY OF
A DROWNING VICTIM.

05:32.506 --> 05:34.203
-YOU'RE KIDDING.

05:34.334 --> 05:36.336
-I'M GONNA NEED TO SEE
YOUR FILES ON THE INCIDENT.

05:36.466 --> 05:37.989
-DON'T TELL ME, THE BOAT FIRE?

05:39.948 --> 05:41.166
WHICH LIFEGUARDS
ARE NAMED IN THE SUIT?

05:41.297 --> 05:42.733
-JUST CAROLINE.

05:42.864 --> 05:44.866
WHY, WERE THERE
OTHERS INVOLVED?

05:44.996 --> 05:46.737
-YOU EVER GET THE FEELING
THAT THERE'S JUST TOO MANY

05:46.868 --> 05:48.348
ATTORNEYS IN THE WORLD?

05:49.305 --> 05:50.654
-I STILL HAVEN'T GOTTEN
A COMPLETE ACCOUNT

05:50.785 --> 05:51.612
OF WHAT HAPPENED THAT NIGHT.

05:51.742 --> 05:53.004
WANNA FILL ME IN?

05:53.570 --> 05:56.225
-BUNCH OF KIDS WERE OUT
ON A BOAT, GETTING ZONKED,

05:56.356 --> 05:58.096
SETTING OFF FIREWORKS.

05:58.227 --> 06:00.795
THEY MANAGED TO SET
THE BOAT ON FIRE.

06:00.925 --> 06:03.841
THEY JUMPED IN THE WATER
TO AVOID THE FLAMES.

06:04.494 --> 06:06.888
CAROLINE WAS THE
FIRST TO RESPOND.

06:22.773 --> 06:26.516
SHE RESCUED THREE OF THE BOYS,
NEWMIE RESCUED THE FOURTH.

06:27.256 --> 06:29.432
-CAROLINE, HOW MANY
WERE ON THE BOAT?

06:33.654 --> 06:34.872
-FOUR.

06:36.526 --> 06:40.008
-PROBLEM WAS, THERE WERE
FIVE BOYS ON THE BOAT.

06:43.054 --> 06:44.578
-SHE MUST'VE BEEN
A WRECK AFTERWARD.

06:45.274 --> 06:46.754
-HER ENTIRE LIFE FELL APART.

06:47.668 --> 06:49.713
IT TOOK A LONG TIME TO PUT
THE PIECES BACK TOGETHER.

06:50.845 --> 06:52.107
-WE CAN'T LET
THAT HAPPEN AGAIN.

06:53.500 --> 06:54.936
WHERE IS SHE?

06:55.066 --> 06:56.198
-HER SHIFT ENDED ABOUT
A HALF AN HOUR AGO.

06:56.851 --> 06:58.069
YOU WANNA TALK TO HER?

06:58.200 --> 06:59.506
-SAM:
YEAH, I BETTER DO THAT.

06:59.636 --> 07:02.944
-DO ME A FAVOR, WILL YA?
GO EASY ON HER?

07:19.874 --> 07:22.746
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

07:53.037 --> 07:54.952
-SAM: I GUESS YOU KNOW.

07:55.083 --> 07:56.998
I'M SO SORRY, CAROLINE.

07:59.217 --> 08:01.132
-THEY CAME RIGHT
UP TO MY TOWER.

08:03.526 --> 08:06.790
THE MOTHER WANTED TO SEE THE
WOMAN WHO LET HER SON DIE.

08:06.921 --> 08:08.357
-YOU DIDN'T LET ANYONE DIE.

08:08.488 --> 08:13.057
-YES, I DID.
YOU WEREN'T THERE.

08:18.846 --> 08:20.804
-I TALKED TO MITCH,
HE TOLD ME WHAT HAPPENED.

08:23.198 --> 08:24.721
-I KNEW THIS WOULDN'T GO AWAY.

08:27.289 --> 08:29.247
I KNEW THAT NO MATTER HOW
HARD I TRIED TO FORGET,

08:29.378 --> 08:31.423
THAT THIS WOULDN'T GO AWAY.

08:34.296 --> 08:36.558
NOW I'VE GOTTA GO
TO COURT AND I HAVE

08:36.690 --> 08:38.429
TO RELIVE THE WHOLE THING.

08:38.561 --> 08:40.389
-I'VE ALREADY TALKED TO THE
LAWYER WHO'S HANDLING THE CASE.

08:40.520 --> 08:42.433
HE SAID NINE TIMES OUT OF TEN,
THESE KIND OF THINGS

08:42.565 --> 08:43.784
ARE DISMISSED OR
SETTLED OUT OF COURT.

08:46.177 --> 08:48.484
YOU'VE BEEN THROUGH SOME
TOUGH TIMES LATELY, I KNOW,

08:48.615 --> 08:49.703
BUT YOU'RE GONNA
GET THROUGH THIS.

08:51.139 --> 08:56.013
PROMISE, NO MATTER WHAT
HAPPENS, WE WILL BE WITH YOU

08:56.144 --> 08:57.885
EVERY STEP OF THE WAY.

08:58.015 --> 09:03.630
[MELANCHOLY MUSIC]

09:03.760 --> 09:05.196
-HAVE YOU HEARD
FROM CAROLINE?

09:05.327 --> 09:06.981
WASN'T SHE SUPPOSED TO
COOK DINNER TONIGHT?

09:07.111 --> 09:08.722
-C.J.: NO, I HAVEN'T HEARD
FROM HER. MAYBE SHE FORGOT.

09:08.852 --> 09:10.506
-THAT'S ALL RIGHT.

09:10.637 --> 09:12.290
MADE A BIG RACE TOMORROW,
JUST GONNA EAT A BIG BOWL

09:12.421 --> 09:13.770
OF PASTA AND GO TO BED EARLY.

09:13.901 --> 09:18.079
-YEAH, THERE YOU GO,
I GAVE YOU A LITTLE TOY.

09:22.257 --> 09:24.520
-C.J., WHERE DID
THAT BABY COME FROM?

09:25.260 --> 09:26.348
-YOU DON'T KNOW WHERE
BABIES COME FROM?

09:26.478 --> 09:28.916
-C.J.
-WE'RE BABYSITTING.

09:29.046 --> 09:30.308
-FOR WHO?

09:30.439 --> 09:32.963
-FOR OUR FRIEND
IN ROBERT DOWN 34D.

09:33.094 --> 09:34.748
THEY HAVEN'T BEEN OUT
BY THEMSELVES SINCE JAMES

09:34.878 --> 09:37.272
WAS BORN, SO I SAID WE'D
LOOK AFTER HIM TONIGHT.

09:38.578 --> 09:41.929
HI, CODY.
MY NAME IS JAMES.

09:43.800 --> 09:45.410
-HEYA, JAMES. HOW'S
IT GOING, BUDDY?

09:45.541 --> 09:47.543
-YOU JUST HAD A
LITTLE NAP, DIDN'T WE?

09:48.022 --> 09:50.067
YOU HUNGRY?
YOU WANT SOME NUMMIES?

09:50.807 --> 09:52.156
-NUMMIES?

09:52.287 --> 09:54.376
-YEAH, I'M GONNA
HEAT UP SOME FORMULA.

09:56.726 --> 09:57.727
HERE.

09:58.815 --> 10:00.469
-[LAUGHS] THAT'S OKAY,
I'M NOT TOO GOOD WITH BABIES.

10:00.600 --> 10:02.297
-NOW'S THE PERFECT
TIME TO LEARN.

10:06.127 --> 10:08.042
PUT YOUR TOWEL DOWN AND
PUT YOUR ARMS OUT STRAIGHT.

10:10.697 --> 10:13.003
THERE, IS THAT COMFORTABLE?

10:13.874 --> 10:15.397
-FOR HIM OR ME?

10:15.527 --> 10:17.355
-WELL, CRADLE HIM IN
YOUR ARMS LIKE A FOOTBALL.

10:18.182 --> 10:19.227
THERE.

10:20.358 --> 10:22.926
-OKAY, NOW WHAT DO I DO?

10:23.057 --> 10:24.711
-SNUGGLE HIM CLOSE
TO YOUR CHEST.

10:27.452 --> 10:29.150
ISN'T HE ADORABLE?

10:29.280 --> 10:31.543
I WANNA HAVE A LITTLE
GUY JUST LIKE THIS.

10:31.674 --> 10:32.806
DON'T YOU?

10:32.936 --> 10:36.505
-YEAH, MAYBE, SOME DAY.

10:37.898 --> 10:39.682
THAT A BOY.
[BABY POOPING]

10:40.248 --> 10:42.554
WHAT'S HE DOING?
OH, NO, OH, NO, NO.

10:42.685 --> 10:46.515
-IT'S YOUR FIRST DIRTY DIAPER.
-NO, C.J. TAKE HIM.

10:46.994 --> 10:49.344
-OH, WHAT ARE YOU
SO SQUEAMISH ABOUT?

10:49.474 --> 10:50.737
IT'S JUST POOPIES.

10:50.867 --> 10:52.347
-I DON'T DO DIAPERS.

10:54.175 --> 10:55.872
-C.J.: MEN ARE SUCH WIMPS.

10:58.396 --> 11:01.051
-OH, GOD.

11:01.182 --> 11:03.271
-THEY'VE ASSIGNED YOU
THE MOST QUALIFIED PERSON

11:03.401 --> 11:04.925
IN THE COUNTY COUNCIL'S OFFICE.

11:05.055 --> 11:07.057
MITCH KNEW HIM, THEY
WENT TO SCHOOL TOGETHER.

11:08.406 --> 11:11.583
STEVE, THIS IS CAROLINE HOLDEN.

11:11.714 --> 11:13.237
-STEVE COST.

11:13.368 --> 11:15.022
-I THOUGHT YOU SAID
THE CHARGES WERE GOING

11:15.152 --> 11:16.501
TO BE DISMISSED.

11:16.632 --> 11:17.720
-THE JUDGE WOULDN'T
GRANT OUR MOTION.

11:19.113 --> 11:20.897
THERE'S STILL A CHANCE
WE WILL REACH A SETTLEMENT,

11:21.028 --> 11:23.639
BUT UNTIL WE HAVE A DEAL,
WE HAVE TO PREPARE FOR TRIAL.

11:24.814 --> 11:28.165
YOU SHOULD ALSO BE AWARE THAT
IN ADDITION TO THE CHARGE

11:28.296 --> 11:30.341
OF NEGLIGENCE, THEY ARE
SEEKING PUNITIVE DAMAGES

11:30.472 --> 11:33.344
AGAINST YOU PERSONALLY
FOR RECKLESS CONDUCT.

11:33.475 --> 11:34.911
-RECKLESS CONDUCT?

11:35.390 --> 11:37.305
WAIT A SECOND,
I DIDN'T ACT RECKLESSLY.

11:37.435 --> 11:39.655
IF ANYBODY ACTED
RECKLESSLY, THOSE BOYS DID.

11:40.351 --> 11:41.875
-HOW MUCH ARE THEY ASKING
IN PUNITIVE DAMAGES?

11:42.005 --> 11:44.704
-TWO MILLION DOLLARS.
-TWO MILLION DOLLARS.

11:44.834 --> 11:47.445
-THE COUNTY WILL DEFEND YOU
ON ALL COUNTS,

11:47.576 --> 11:49.143
BUT IF A JURY SHOULD
FIND AGAINST YOU

11:49.273 --> 11:51.798
ON THE RECKLESS CONDUCT
CHARGES, YOU COULD BE PERSONALLY

11:51.928 --> 11:53.147
LIABLE FOR THOSE DAMAGES.

11:56.150 --> 11:57.412
-THEY KNOW THERE'S
NO WAY SHE CAN COME UP

11:57.542 --> 11:58.892
WITH TWO MILLION DOLLARS.

11:59.022 --> 12:00.458
-THEY ARE USING THAT FIGURE
AS LEVERAGE

12:00.589 --> 12:01.764
FOR SETTLEMENT PURPOSES.

12:01.895 --> 12:03.592
IT'S HIGHLY
UNLIKELY ANY JURY

12:03.723 --> 12:06.073
WOULD AWARD THAT MUCH,
BUT THESE DAYS, WHO KNOWS.

12:06.203 --> 12:08.902
-MM-HM, SO THEY COULD JUST
TAKE EVERYTHING THAT I HAVE.

12:09.032 --> 12:11.687
-THESE ARE VERY SERIOUS
CHARGES, CAROLINE.

12:21.305 --> 12:27.050
[CALMING MUSIC]

12:47.244 --> 12:48.376
-MAN: HEY, MAN.

12:50.857 --> 12:51.988
-WOMAN: GOOD LUCK!

12:58.342 --> 13:01.171
[THRILLING MUSIC]

13:18.319 --> 13:21.104
[CHEERING]

13:22.671 --> 13:23.628
[GUNSHOT FIRING]

14:28.258 --> 14:29.303
-DRIVE ME.

15:57.086 --> 15:59.436
[CHEERING]

16:01.873 --> 16:04.093
-WHOO!

16:06.095 --> 16:10.926
-YES! WHOO!

16:14.799 --> 16:16.540
-CONGRATULATIONS.
-ALL RIGHT, THANK YOU.

16:16.671 --> 16:18.760
-GOOD RACE, MAN. GOOD RACE.

16:18.890 --> 16:21.545
-WHOO-HOO! YES!

16:21.676 --> 16:24.113
BABY, COME HERE. YEAH.

16:24.244 --> 16:25.985
-GOOD JOB.

16:26.115 --> 16:28.248
-CONGRATULATIONS, THAT WAS
A HELL OF A RACE YOU JUST RAN.

16:28.378 --> 16:29.466
THANK YOU.
-KEITH: KEITH CURBY.

16:29.597 --> 16:30.990
-CODY MADISON.

16:31.120 --> 16:32.339
-HOW LONG HAVE YOU BEEN
RACING MOUNTAIN BIKES?

16:32.469 --> 16:34.341
-ACTUALLY, I JUST
STARTED, THIS IS

16:34.471 --> 16:36.038
MY FIRST
SERIOUS COMPETITION.

16:36.169 --> 16:37.909
-REALLY, YOU KNOW
I REPRESENT A LOT OF THE GUYS

16:38.040 --> 16:39.476
IN THE PRO CIRCUIT.

16:39.607 --> 16:40.651
I WAS HOPING WE MIGHT
BE ABLE TO SIT DOWN

16:40.782 --> 16:42.914
SOMETIME AND CHAT.
-YEAH?

16:43.045 --> 16:45.482
-BETWEEN THE EVENTS THEMSELVES
AND THE ENDORSEMENTS,

16:45.613 --> 16:47.528
A GUY LIKE YOU COULD MAKE
AN AWFUL LOT OF MONEY.

16:48.007 --> 16:49.356
-I LIKE THE SOUND OF THAT.

16:49.486 --> 16:51.010
-THE COMPANIES THAT
SPONSOR THE TOUR

16:51.140 --> 16:52.620
ABSOLUTELY ARE DYING
TO FIND SOMEONE

16:52.750 --> 16:54.317
TO PITCH THEIR PRODUCTS.

16:54.448 --> 16:56.102
YOU MIGHT HAVE THE POTENTIAL
TO BE THAT SOMEONE.

16:57.407 --> 17:01.803
[SOOTHING MUSIC]

17:10.811 --> 17:13.380
-LET'S START WITH
A FEW GENERAL QUESTIONS

17:13.510 --> 17:16.035
BEFORE WE GET INTO THE
SPECIFICS OF THE CASE.

17:17.384 --> 17:18.819
YOU ARE HOW OLD?

17:19.560 --> 17:20.691
-CAROLINE: 26.

17:20.821 --> 17:21.953
-MARITAL STATUS?

17:22.998 --> 17:24.304
-CAROLINE: I'M DIVORCED.

17:24.913 --> 17:27.349
-ME, TOO. SUCKS.

17:28.134 --> 17:29.222
ANY KIDS?

17:30.049 --> 17:31.180
-NO.

17:31.702 --> 17:33.052
-EDUCATION?

17:33.617 --> 17:36.794
-CAROLINE: I'VE A BACHELOR'S
DEGREE FROM SAN DIEGO STATE.

17:38.013 --> 17:40.146
-THAT'S WHERE I WENT TO SCHOOL.
WHAT YEAR DID YOU GRADUATE?

17:40.885 --> 17:42.104
-'92.

17:42.800 --> 17:48.067
-[LAUGHS] I WAS
A LITTLE BIT BEFORE THAT.

17:50.982 --> 17:52.854
HOW LONG HAVE YOU
BEEN LIFEGUARDING?

17:53.594 --> 17:54.725
-THREE YEARS.

17:55.596 --> 17:58.077
-HAVE YOU EVER
PARTICIPATED IN A RESCUE

17:58.207 --> 18:00.557
THAT RESULTED
IN A FATALITY BEFORE?

18:01.428 --> 18:02.472
-NO.

18:08.870 --> 18:11.786
-STEVE: I'M SURE THIS WAS
A VERY TRAUMATIC EXPERIENCE

18:11.916 --> 18:14.702
FOR YOU AND NOT SOMETHING
YOU WANT TO RELIVE,

18:16.443 --> 18:18.836
BUT I NEED TO KNOW EXACTLY
WHAT HAPPENED THAT NIGHT.

18:21.752 --> 18:22.971
TAKE YOUR TIME.

18:24.451 --> 18:26.670
TRY TO REMEMBER AS
MUCH DETAIL AS YOU CAN.

18:34.591 --> 18:37.072
-I WAS WORKING A
DOUBLE SHIFT THAT DAY.

18:41.859 --> 18:46.603
I WENT OUT ONTO THE SCARAB JUST
BEFORE THE SUN WAS SETTING.

18:49.258 --> 18:52.131
I REMEMBER WHAT A BEAUTIFUL
SUNSET IT REALLY WAS.

18:52.870 --> 18:55.830
295 FROM BAYWATCH SCARAB ONE.
I'M ON PATROL

18:55.960 --> 18:57.658
NORTHBOUND OUT OF
MARINA DEL REY.

18:58.702 --> 19:00.878
ABOUT AN HOUR AFTER IT GOT DARK,

19:01.966 --> 19:04.055
I NOTICED SOMEONE
SHOOTING OFF FIREWORKS,

19:04.186 --> 19:06.014
SO I HEADED
IN THAT DIRECTION.

19:07.537 --> 19:09.931
[BOYS SHOUTING]

19:12.281 --> 19:15.154
AS SOON AS I SAW THE FLAMES,
I CALLED FOR BACK UP.

19:18.374 --> 19:21.856
BY THE TIME... I GOT
THERE, EVERYONE HAD

19:21.986 --> 19:23.945
ALREADY JUMPED OVERBOARD.

19:24.075 --> 19:29.646
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]
[SHOUTING]

19:47.577 --> 19:49.405
[COUGHING]

20:01.330 --> 20:05.116
WHEN I REACHED THE FIRST
VICTIM, I REMEMBER HIM AS BEING

20:05.247 --> 20:07.510
ONE OF THE BOYS I HAD
SEEN EARLIER THAT MORNING.

20:08.119 --> 20:09.295
-WHERE DID YOU SEE HIM?

20:10.600 --> 20:12.080
-THEY WERE CRUISING THE MARINA.

20:13.995 --> 20:15.779
THEY WERE ACTING LIKE
A BUNCH OF JERKS.

20:16.606 --> 20:18.304
-HOW MANY BOYS DID
YOU SEE ON THE BOAT?

20:19.087 --> 20:20.088
-I SAW FIVE.

20:20.219 --> 20:21.350
-YOU'RE POSITIVE IT WAS FIVE?

20:21.481 --> 20:22.786
-YES.

20:22.917 --> 20:24.527
-THEN, WHY DID YOU
ONLY RESCUE FOUR?

20:24.658 --> 20:26.964
WAS IT A MENTAL LAPSE?
DID IT SLIP YOUR MIND?

20:27.095 --> 20:28.792
-NO.

20:28.923 --> 20:30.577
-YOU SAID YOU HAD BEEN WORKING
A DOUBLE SHIFT, WERE YOU TIRED?

20:30.707 --> 20:32.840
-NO, I WASN'T.
-SO THEN, YOU JUST SCREWED UP, THAT'S IT?

20:33.493 --> 20:36.017
-WHY ARE YOU ATTACKING ME?
-ANSWER THE QUESTION.

20:36.147 --> 20:39.020
WHY DID YOU ONLY THINK THERE
WERE FOUR BOYS IN THAT BOAT?

20:39.150 --> 20:42.545
-BECAUSE THE NEXT TIME I SAW
THEM, THERE WERE ONLY FOUR.

20:42.676 --> 20:43.720
-AND WHEN WAS THAT?

20:44.504 --> 20:47.507
-WHEN I GOT ON TO THE SCARAB.
IT WAS TIED TO THE DOCK.

20:47.637 --> 20:50.945
I DIDN'T SEE THE BOY
IN THE COWBOY HAT.

20:51.075 --> 20:53.339
-YOU DIDN'T SEE HIM OR YOU
DON'T REMEMBER SEEING HIM?

20:53.469 --> 20:54.905
-I DIDN'T SEE HIM.

20:55.036 --> 20:56.864
-DID YOU WONDER WHAT
MAYBE HAPPENED TO HIM?

20:56.994 --> 20:59.432
-NO.
-DID THE THOUGHT EVEN CROSS YOUR MIND?

20:59.562 --> 21:02.086
-LOOK, I DIDN'T THINK
ABOUT IT, I DIDN'T KNOW

21:02.217 --> 21:03.566
HE WAS GONNA DIE.

21:03.697 --> 21:05.176
-IS THAT WHY THAT
BOY DIED, CAROLINE,

21:05.307 --> 21:06.656
BECAUSE YOU WERE NOT THINKING?

21:08.310 --> 21:11.052
CAROLINE, WHAT WAS
GOING THROUGH YOUR MIND?

21:12.401 --> 21:15.274
-SAVE ME, MA'AM. I'M DRUNK
IN MY SUDS. PLEASE HELP ME.

21:15.404 --> 21:16.623
-STEVE: CAROLINE.

21:17.667 --> 21:19.495
-SAVE ME. [LAUGHS]

21:19.626 --> 21:21.105
-STEVE: CAROLINE.

21:21.758 --> 21:25.327
-YOU DON'T REMEMBER HIM?
HOW COULD YOU FORGET?

21:25.458 --> 21:26.850
[LAUGHING]

21:28.287 --> 21:30.245
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

21:41.256 --> 21:43.737
[MELANCHOLY MUSIC]

21:47.349 --> 21:50.961
-$500,000?
THIS ISN'T A SETTLEMENT.

21:51.092 --> 21:52.311
IT'S A SURRENDER.

21:52.441 --> 21:53.964
-THE COUNTY WILL
PAY THE FULL AMOUNT.

21:54.095 --> 21:56.010
NOTHING WILL COME OUT
OF CAROLINE'S POCKET.

21:56.140 --> 21:57.751
-WELL, I FIND IT HARD TO
BELIEVE THIS IS THE BEST

21:57.881 --> 21:59.448
THAT YOU CAN DO.

21:59.579 --> 22:01.494
-THE BOARD OF SUPERVISORS
IS WORRIED ABOUT A JURY

22:01.624 --> 22:03.017
AWARDING THE FULL AMOUNT.

22:03.147 --> 22:05.236
THEY DO NOT WANT TO PART
WITH TWO MILLION DOLLARS

22:05.367 --> 22:06.760
OF TAX PAYERS' MONEY.

22:06.890 --> 22:08.544
-I THOUGHT YOU SAID
WE HAD A GOOD CASE.

22:08.675 --> 22:10.633
-WE DO, AS LONG AS CAROLINE
ISN'T CALLED TO TESTIFY.

22:11.547 --> 22:13.854
WE COULD NOT EVEN GET THROUGH
A PRELIMINARY INTERVIEW.

22:13.984 --> 22:15.638
SHE'LL NEVER HOLD UP
ON THE WITNESS STAND.

22:15.769 --> 22:17.161
-ISN'T THAT YOUR JOB?

22:17.292 --> 22:18.946
AREN'T YOU SUPPOSED
TO PREPARE HER FOR THAT?

22:19.076 --> 22:21.905
-I CAN PREPARE HER UNTIL
WE ARE BOTH BLUE IN THE FACE,

22:22.036 --> 22:24.734
BUT IF SHE STILL BLAMES
HERSELF FOR THAT BOY'S DEATH,

22:24.865 --> 22:26.345
IT'S GOING TO COME OUT
IN HER TESTIMONY.

22:26.475 --> 22:28.999
BELIEVE ME, I KNOW
THE OPPOSING ATTORNEY.

22:29.478 --> 22:30.914
SHE'LL EAT HER ALIVE.

22:32.742 --> 22:33.787
-THEY'VE AGREED TO THIS?

22:33.917 --> 22:35.354
-NO, NOT YET.

22:35.484 --> 22:37.399
COWBOY'S MOM IS STILL
DEMANDING THAT CAROLINE

22:37.530 --> 22:39.096
BE DISMISSED FROM
THE DEPARTMENT.

22:39.227 --> 22:41.272
BELIEVE IT OR NOT, THE
MONEY IS SECONDARY TO HER.

22:42.056 --> 22:43.753
-SO THEY JUST
WANT HER TO SUFFER.

22:44.232 --> 22:45.538
WHAT IS THIS,
A PERSONAL VENDETTA?

22:45.668 --> 22:47.670
[PHONE RINGING]
-EXCUSE ME.

22:49.933 --> 22:53.110
HELLO. YEAH, PUT HER THROUGH.

22:53.241 --> 22:54.721
IT'S
THE PLAINTIFF'S ATTORNEY.

22:54.851 --> 22:58.594
ELLEN, HELLO.
SO DO WE HAVE A DEAL?

23:00.857 --> 23:02.946
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

23:12.913 --> 23:15.002
-HI, CAROLINE.
-HEY.

23:17.918 --> 23:19.398
-I'M REALLY SORRY ABOUT
THE RINGER THEY'RE PUTTING

23:19.528 --> 23:20.834
YOU THROUGH ON THIS.

23:20.964 --> 23:22.488
IF THERE'S ANYTHING I CAN DO.

23:23.663 --> 23:24.620
-THANKS.

23:30.452 --> 23:31.671
YOU HEARD SOMETHING.

23:32.454 --> 23:34.108
-THEY COULDN'T
REACH A SETTLEMENT.

23:34.238 --> 23:36.023
-I KNEW I WAS GOING
TO HAVE TO GO TO COURT.

23:36.153 --> 23:38.460
-YOU ARE NOT GOING
TO COURT. NOT YET ANYWAY.

23:39.548 --> 23:40.723
NOW THE PLAINTIFF HAS
AGREED TO TAKE THE CASE

23:40.854 --> 23:42.421
TO ARBITRATION.

23:42.551 --> 23:44.597
NOW IF EVERYONE ACCEPTS
THE ARBITRATOR'S RULING,

23:44.727 --> 23:47.164
THEN THAT WILL BE IT,
HIS DECISION IS FINAL.

23:48.514 --> 23:50.124
-COME ON, WHAT
DIFFERENCE DOES IT MAKE?

23:50.820 --> 23:52.387
EITHER WAY,
I'M STILL ON TRIAL.

23:52.909 --> 23:55.738
[MELANCHOLY MUSIC]

24:08.751 --> 24:10.274
-WELL, HOW LONG
HAVE YOU BEEN UP?

24:11.624 --> 24:13.582
-I'VE HARDLY SLEPT.

24:14.409 --> 24:17.717
-OH, YOU POOR THING.
THIS IS SO UNFAIR.

24:17.847 --> 24:20.328
-THEY SHOULD BE TREATING YOU
LIKE A HERO, NOT A CRIMINAL.

24:20.459 --> 24:22.852
THIS SYSTEM IS SO SCREWED UP,
I COULD SCREAM.

24:23.418 --> 24:25.202
-PROBABLY WON'T BE
SUCH A GOOD IDEA.

24:25.333 --> 24:26.726
MIGHT WAKE THE NEIGHBORS.

24:26.856 --> 24:29.380
[LAUGHING]

24:29.511 --> 24:32.514
-GEEZ, HOW LONG IS CODY
GOING TO BE IN THERE?

24:32.645 --> 24:35.691
-OH, I'M SORRY,
HE TOLD ME TO TELL YOU THAT

24:35.822 --> 24:37.606
HE WENT MOUNTAIN BIKE
RIDING AND THAT HE HAD SOME

24:37.737 --> 24:38.781
MEETING WITH A SPORTS AGENT.

24:38.912 --> 24:40.000
WHAT IS THAT ABOUT?

24:40.130 --> 24:41.915
-OH.

24:42.045 --> 24:43.917
THEY WANT HIM TO
BE A PROFESSIONAL
MOUNTAIN BIKE RACER.

24:44.047 --> 24:46.267
-OH. [LAUGHS]

24:47.007 --> 24:49.052
WOULDN'T THAT MAKE
HIM TRAVEL A LOT?

24:49.183 --> 24:51.490
-YEAH, BUT IT'S
PROBABLY JUST AS WELL.

24:55.929 --> 24:57.844
I THINK CODY AND I HAVE
COME TO THE END OF OUR ROAD.

24:57.974 --> 25:00.411
-WHAT? WHAT ARE
YOU TALKING ABOUT?

25:00.542 --> 25:01.935
-I DON'T KNOW, I DON'T
KNOW WHAT'S COME OVER ME.

25:02.065 --> 25:03.763
ALL I CAN THINK ABOUT
IS HAVING A BABY.

25:03.893 --> 25:05.591
I HAVE ALL THESE MATERNAL
FEELINGS AND I HAVE

25:05.721 --> 25:08.115
NO WAY TO EXPRESS THEM EXCEPT

25:08.245 --> 25:09.856
FOR WHEN
I'M BABYSITTING JAMES.

25:09.986 --> 25:12.032
WHICH REMINDS ME, I'M LOOKING
AFTER HIM THIS MORNING.

25:12.162 --> 25:13.903
-OH, THAT'S OKAY.

25:14.034 --> 25:15.992
LISTEN, HAVE YOU TALKED TO
CODY ABOUT STARTING A FAMILY?

25:16.123 --> 25:17.951
-HE'S NOT READY.

25:18.081 --> 25:20.257
HE'S OUT THERE LOOKING
FOR ACTION AND ADVENTURE.

25:20.823 --> 25:22.259
HE'S NOT READY TO SETTLE DOWN.

25:23.696 --> 25:25.001
WHICH IS PERFECTLY
UNDERSTANDABLE, I MEAN,

25:25.132 --> 25:26.655
THAT'S JUST THE WAY HE IS.

25:26.786 --> 25:28.657
I DON'T KNOW HOW MUCH
LONGER I CAN WAIT.

25:28.788 --> 25:30.746
MY BIOLOGICAL CLOCK IS TICKING.

25:30.877 --> 25:33.662
-[LAUGHS] OH, C.J.,
I'M PRETTY SURE THAT GOT

25:33.793 --> 25:35.316
A COUPLE OF TICKS
LEFT IN YOU.

25:37.753 --> 25:39.059
-OH, I'M SORRY,
I SHOULDN'T BE BOTHERING YOU

25:39.189 --> 25:40.234
WITH ALL MY STUPID PROBLEMS.

25:40.364 --> 25:41.148
YOU HAVE ENOUGH ON YOUR MIND.

25:41.278 --> 25:42.323
-OH, NO, THAT'S OKAY.

25:42.453 --> 25:43.977
I MEAN, WHAT ARE FRIENDS FOR?

25:44.543 --> 25:47.197
BESIDES, IT'S KIND OF NICE
TO KNOW THERE'S SOMEBODY

25:47.328 --> 25:49.156
OUT THERE WHO'S AS
DEPRESSED AS I AM.

25:50.810 --> 25:52.289
[LAUGHING]

25:53.073 --> 25:54.422
-LET'S GO EAT SOMETHING.

25:56.729 --> 25:59.558
[SOFT MUSIC]

26:24.060 --> 26:26.454
♪ I'VE BEEN

26:26.585 --> 26:30.023
♪ WAITING FOR THE TIME TO PASS

26:30.153 --> 26:33.330
♪ STARING AT THE HOUR GLASS

26:33.461 --> 26:37.073
♪ OOH

26:37.204 --> 26:40.773
♪ HOPING

26:40.903 --> 26:44.298
♪ FOR WHAT MY FUTURE HOLDS

26:44.428 --> 26:47.170
♪ CAN'T HELP BUT WANT MORE

26:47.301 --> 26:49.782
♪ OOH

26:51.522 --> 26:55.918
♪ THINKING OF YOU FEELS LIKE A DREAM

26:58.399 --> 27:02.621
♪ THE FUTURES CLOSER THAN IT SEEMS

27:04.753 --> 27:10.019
♪ THERE'S SOMETHING IN THE WAY
♪ YOU MAKE ME FEEL

27:11.934 --> 27:15.198
♪ THERE'S SOMETHING BOUT THE WAY I KNOW

27:15.329 --> 27:18.288
♪ INSIDE IT FEELS SO REAL

27:18.419 --> 27:23.424
♪ WON'T SPEND TIME WISHING ON THE STARS

27:25.295 --> 27:29.865
♪ CAUSE I KNOW SOMEDAY
♪ I'LL FEEL YOU IN MY ARMS

27:32.128 --> 27:37.264
♪ SOMEDAY I'LL FEEL YOU IN MY ARMS

27:39.048 --> 27:44.619
♪ SOMEDAY I'LL FEEL YOU IN MY ARMS

27:50.581 --> 27:55.456
-CAROLINE, YOU CAN EITHER
KEEP FEELING SORRY FOR YOURSELF

27:55.586 --> 27:57.676
OR YOU CAN START HELPING
ME PREPARE YOUR DEFENSE.

27:58.328 --> 27:59.678
IT'S YOUR CHOICE.

28:02.332 --> 28:03.812
-WHAT DO YOU THINK
OUR CHANCES ARE?

28:03.943 --> 28:06.510
-HONESTLY, IT
COULD GO EITHER WAY.

28:06.641 --> 28:09.296
-GOOD. THAT'S ENCOURAGING.

28:09.818 --> 28:12.212
-I WOULD FEEL
A LOT MORE CONFIDENT

28:12.342 --> 28:13.517
IF I HAD YOUR COOPERATION.

28:17.086 --> 28:18.305
I MIGHT EVEN BE
ABLE TO HELP YOU.

28:18.435 --> 28:20.437
-WELL, MAYBE
I DON'T WANT YOUR HELP.

28:22.439 --> 28:24.224
MAYBE I DON'T DESERVE
TO BE OUT THERE.

28:26.313 --> 28:27.314
-YOU REALLY BELIEVE THAT?

28:31.405 --> 28:32.362
-I DON'T KNOW.

28:36.932 --> 28:39.239
-I NEVER KNEW YOUR SISTER,
BUT I SURE HEARD A LOT

28:39.369 --> 28:41.241
ABOUT HER WHEN I WAS
WORKING DOWN IN SOUTH BAY.

28:42.155 --> 28:44.070
SHE WAS LIKE A LIVING
LEGEND DOWN THERE.

28:45.071 --> 28:47.073
THE NAME STEPHANIE
HOLDEN WAS SYNONYMOUS

28:47.203 --> 28:49.423
WITH PRIDE AND GUTS AND COURAGE.

28:50.163 --> 28:52.034
MOST IMPORTANTLY
PROFESSIONALISM.

28:53.557 --> 28:56.082
I'M JUST REALLY SORRY IT
DOESN'T RUN IN THE FAMILY.

28:58.606 --> 29:00.564
IF YOU DECIDE YOU WANT
TO STAND UP AND FIGHT,

29:01.522 --> 29:02.653
NOT JUST FOR YOURSELF,

29:03.654 --> 29:05.308
BUT FOR
EVERY LIFEGUARD OUT THERE,

29:05.961 --> 29:07.267
YOU CAN REACH ME
AT MY OFFICE.

29:09.399 --> 29:10.531
-STEVE?

29:36.513 --> 29:39.865
I KNOW THAT I DID ALL
I COULD TO SAVE THOSE BOYS.

29:41.780 --> 29:43.912
I DON'T THINK
I DESERVE TO BE PUNISHED.

29:44.043 --> 29:49.700
-NEITHER DO I, BUT WE STILL
HAVE TO CONVINCE AN ARBITRATOR.

29:54.618 --> 29:56.707
-I'LL DO THE BEST
THAT I CAN.

30:02.626 --> 30:06.239
[MELANCHOLY MUSIC]

30:13.942 --> 30:15.814
-GOOD MORNING,
LADIES AND GENTLEMEN.

30:15.944 --> 30:19.556
I'M JUDGE WILLIAM LANG
AND I'LL BE ARBITRATING

30:19.687 --> 30:21.210
THESE PROCEEDINGS TODAY.

30:21.994 --> 30:24.170
SO, MS. DOUGLAS,
IF YOU ARE READY,

30:24.300 --> 30:26.476
YOU MAY PROCEED WITH
YOUR FIRST WITNESS.

30:28.000 --> 30:30.089
-MRS. O'HARA, HOW OLD
WAS YOUR SON THOMAS

30:30.219 --> 30:31.394
WHEN HE DIED?

30:32.352 --> 30:33.832
-NINETEEN.

30:33.962 --> 30:37.748
-NINETEEN YEARS OLD.
STILL LIVING AT HOME?

30:37.879 --> 30:42.753
-YES, HE WAS
TRYING TO SAVE MONEY

30:42.884 --> 30:44.407
TO GO TO COLLEGE.

30:44.538 --> 30:49.021
HE WANTED TO BE A TEACHER.
HE LOVED CHILDREN.

30:49.804 --> 30:52.198
-HIS FRIENDS CALLED
HIM COWBOY, DIDN'T THEY?

30:52.328 --> 30:56.724
-YEAH, WELL, I HAD
GIVEN HIM A COWBOY HAT

30:57.464 --> 30:58.726
FOR HIS LAST BIRTHDAY.

30:59.553 --> 31:01.468
IT SEEMED LIKE HE
NEVER TOOK IT OFF.

31:01.598 --> 31:04.558
-WHEN YOU WERE FIRST
INFORMED OF YOUR SON'S DEATH,

31:04.688 --> 31:06.647
YOU WERE TOLD IT
WAS AN ACCIDENT.

31:06.777 --> 31:10.085
-YES, AN ACCIDENTAL DROWNING.

31:11.217 --> 31:14.524
-AND YOU HAD NO INTENTION
OF SUING THE COUNTY

31:14.655 --> 31:16.483
OR THE LIFEGUARDS
FOR WRONGFUL DEATH.

31:16.613 --> 31:18.093
-I TOOK THEIR WORD FOR IT.

31:18.833 --> 31:20.400
-WHAT MADE YOU
CHANGE YOUR MIND?

31:20.530 --> 31:23.838
-I SAW A COPY
OF THE TRANSCRIPT

31:25.840 --> 31:30.410
OF THE DEBRIEFING THEY
HELD AFTER THE INCIDENT.

31:30.540 --> 31:34.936
-A DOCUMENT IN WHICH
CAROLINE HOLDEN CLEARLY STATES

31:35.067 --> 31:39.898
AND I QUOTE, "I SHOULD'VE
KNOWN, THEY WENT PAST ME

31:40.028 --> 31:42.378
"IN THE MARINA, I SAW THEM.

31:42.509 --> 31:47.035
"HE WORE A COWBOY HAT ON
A BOAT. HE FLIRTED WITH ME.

31:47.644 --> 31:50.604
I SHOULDN'T HAVE
FORGOTTEN HIM."

31:51.170 --> 31:52.475
END QUOTE.

31:53.650 --> 31:56.610
-SHE KNEW MY SON
WAS ON THAT BOAT.

31:57.350 --> 31:59.352
AND SHE MAY HAVE
SAVED THE OTHERS,

32:00.570 --> 32:02.703
BUT SHE LET HIM DIE.

32:11.146 --> 32:12.278
-IT'S IN THIS PARAGRAPH.

32:12.408 --> 32:15.150
-UH-HUH, PERFECT, GREAT.

32:15.281 --> 32:17.283
-WHEN YOU FIRST ARRIVED
ON THE SCENE IN YOUR BOAT,

32:17.413 --> 32:19.589
WHERE WAS CAROLINE HOLDEN?

32:19.720 --> 32:21.591
-IN THE WATER.
SHE HAD SECURED TWO VICTIMS

32:21.722 --> 32:23.767
TO HER RESCUE CAN AND
WAS DIVING FOR A THIRD.

32:23.898 --> 32:26.205
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

32:40.262 --> 32:41.263
-HELP!

32:43.918 --> 32:45.311
-I SAW SOMEONE GO
DOWN OVER THERE.

32:45.441 --> 32:46.790
-CAROLINE: OKAY.

32:52.231 --> 32:55.147
-ELLEN: AND YOU FOUND
NO FAULT WITH HER EFFORTS?

32:55.277 --> 32:57.932
-SHE WAS ACTING
EXACTLY ACCORDING TO
LIFEGUARD PROCEDURE.

32:58.063 --> 33:00.674
-HAS IT ALWAYS BEEN
THAT WAY WITH MS. HOLDEN?

33:01.457 --> 33:04.156
OR HAS SHE HAD PROBLEMS
CARRYING OUT HER DUTIES

33:04.286 --> 33:05.635
IN THE PAST?

33:05.766 --> 33:06.985
-I DON'T KNOW WHAT
YOU'RE REFERRING TO.

33:08.073 --> 33:11.859
-I HAVE HERE A SERIES OF
INCIDENT REPORTS IN WHICH

33:11.990 --> 33:15.254
EITHER YOU OR ONE OF YOUR
COLLEAGUES CRITICIZED

33:15.384 --> 33:19.171
THE DEFENDANT'S PERFORMANCE
AND QUESTION HER COMPETENCE.

33:24.480 --> 33:26.526
-MAYBE WHEN SHE FIRST
STARTED AT BAYWATCH.

33:26.656 --> 33:29.529
IT TAKES AWHILE FOR
ROOKIES TO LEARN THE ROPES.

33:29.659 --> 33:32.749
BUT ON THE NIGHT IN QUESTION,
CAROLINE DID EVERYTHING

33:32.880 --> 33:34.621
SHE COULD TO SAVE
THOSE BOYS' LIVES.

33:44.196 --> 33:47.068
-LIEUTENANT BUCHANNON,
YOU CONDUCTED AN INQUIRY

33:47.199 --> 33:49.679
INTO THE DEATH OF
THOMAS EDWARD O'HARA.

33:49.810 --> 33:51.986
WHAT WERE YOU ABLE
TO DETERMINE?

33:52.117 --> 33:56.034
-GIVEN THE CIRCUMSTANCES,
THE BOAT WAS ON FIRE,

33:56.164 --> 33:59.124
MULTIPLE RESCUES IN THE
WATER, THE CONDITION

33:59.254 --> 34:02.779
OF THE VICTIMS, THAT THE
LIFEGUARDS' EFFORTS WERE NOTHING

34:02.910 --> 34:04.651
SHORT OF MIRACULOUS.

34:07.697 --> 34:10.570
-WERE YOU THE ONLY OFFICER
TO SIGN OFF ON A REPORT

34:10.699 --> 34:13.485
WHICH EXONERATED
MS. HOLDEN OF ANY WRONG DOING?

34:13.616 --> 34:14.574
-NO.

34:15.531 --> 34:19.534
-WAS THE OFFICER
LIEUTENANT STEPHANIE HOLDEN?

34:19.666 --> 34:21.014
-YES.

34:21.146 --> 34:22.973
-CAROLINE HOLDEN'S SISTER?

34:23.103 --> 34:27.891
-YES, BUT IF YOU'RE IMPLYING
THAT LIEUTENANT STEPHANIE

34:28.022 --> 34:29.589
HOLDEN LIED TO PREVENT--

34:29.719 --> 34:33.158
-THANK YOU, MR. BUCHANNON.
NO FURTHER QUESTIONS.

34:34.463 --> 34:35.420
-LIEUTENANT BUCHANNON.

34:37.074 --> 34:40.513
YOU STATED IN YOUR REVIEW THAT
THE VICTIM'S BLOOD ALCOHOL

34:40.643 --> 34:41.905
LEVEL WAS 1.9.

34:42.819 --> 34:45.605
-THE CORONER STATED THAT
THE BOY WAS LEGALLY DRUNK

34:45.735 --> 34:47.085
AT THE TIME OF HIS DEATH.

34:47.215 --> 34:49.261
-I IMAGINE THAT MADE IT
DIFFICULT TO SWIM.

34:49.391 --> 34:52.264
-THAT MUCH ALCOHOL WOULD
MAKE IT VERY DIFFICULT

34:52.393 --> 34:53.264
TO WALK LET ALONE SWIM.

34:53.395 --> 34:54.875
-OBJECTION.

34:55.484 --> 34:56.572
-SUSTAINED.

34:56.703 --> 34:58.748
-LET ME REPHRASE
THE QUESTION.

34:59.619 --> 35:02.404
IN YOUR EXPERIENCE AS
A LIFEGUARD, HAVE YOU FOUND

35:02.535 --> 35:05.407
THAT EXCESSIVE CONSUMPTION
OF ALCOHOL CAN IMPEDE

35:05.538 --> 35:07.017
A PERSON'S ABILITY TO SWIM?

35:07.148 --> 35:08.454
-ABSOLUTELY.

35:08.932 --> 35:11.109
IF THAT BOY HAD BEEN
ABLE TO STAY AFLOAT,

35:12.066 --> 35:14.547
I GUARANTEE YOU ONE OF MY
LIFEGUARDS WOULD'VE RESCUED HIM.

35:18.464 --> 35:20.901
-IS IT FAIR TO SAY THAT YOU
HAD DIFFICULTY IN DEALING

35:21.031 --> 35:23.208
WITH THOMAS O'HARA'S DEATH?

35:24.165 --> 35:27.603
-I SUFFERED POST
TRAUMATIC STRESS, YES.

35:27.734 --> 35:30.954
-WHICH INCLUDED EXCESSIVE
DRINKING, STAYING OUT ALL NIGHT,

35:31.085 --> 35:34.480
FAILING TO PASS A LIFEGUARD
RECHECK AND ULTIMATELY

35:34.610 --> 35:36.395
QUITTING YOUR JOB
AT BAYWATCH.

35:36.525 --> 35:40.050
-BUT FORTUNATELY I WAS ABLE
TO RECOVER AND RETURN TO WORK.

35:41.095 --> 35:44.490
-MS. HOLDEN, WHEN WAS THE
FIRST TIME YOU SAW THE BOAT

35:45.055 --> 35:46.187
WITH THE FIVE BOYS ON IT?

35:48.537 --> 35:50.148
-EARLIER THAT AFTERNOON.

35:50.278 --> 35:52.672
-AND THEN AGAIN IN THE
EVENING AS YOU WERE PREPARING

35:52.802 --> 35:54.717
FOR NIGHT PATROL,
IS THAT CORRECT?

35:54.848 --> 35:55.892
-YES.

35:56.676 --> 35:59.069
-IT'S ILLEGAL TO DRIVE
A WATER CRAFT WHILE

35:59.200 --> 36:01.855
UNDER THE INFLUENCE OF
ALCOHOL, ISN'T IT, MS. HOLDEN?

36:02.421 --> 36:03.770
-YES.

36:03.900 --> 36:05.859
-YET YOU MADE NO ATTEMPT
TO STOP THOSE BOYS

36:05.989 --> 36:08.035
OR TO CONFISCATE
THEIR BEER.

36:08.166 --> 36:12.257
EVEN THOUGH AS A LIFEGUARD,
YOU HAD THE AUTHORITY TO DO SO.

36:12.387 --> 36:14.781
-COME ON, GUYS, PUT
AWAY THE BEER, ALL RIGHT?

36:14.911 --> 36:16.174
WE'RE GONNA HAVE
TO CONFISCATE IT.

36:16.304 --> 36:18.263
-SAVE ME, MA'AM,
I'M DROWNING IN MY SUDS.

36:18.393 --> 36:20.352
PLEASE, HELP ME, SAVE ME.

36:23.050 --> 36:25.574
-I TOLD THEM THAT THEY
SHOULDN'T GO OUT ON THAT BOAT.

36:25.705 --> 36:28.229
-OH, AND WHAT WAS
THEIR RESPONSE?

36:28.360 --> 36:30.275
-THEY PAID
NO ATTENTION TO ME.

36:30.405 --> 36:33.539
-SO, YOU LET THEM GO,
EVEN THOUGH YOU SUSPECTED

36:33.669 --> 36:36.498
THAT THEY WERE INTOXICATED
AND MIGHT ENDANGER

36:36.629 --> 36:38.152
THEMSELVES
OR OTHER BOATERS.

36:38.283 --> 36:41.242
SO, PERHAPS THIS SENSELESS
TRAGEDY MIGHT NEVER

36:41.373 --> 36:44.898
HAVE OCCURRED IF YOU HADN'T
NEGLECTED TO ENFORCE THE LAW.

36:45.028 --> 36:49.076
-OBJECTION, THE DEFENDANT IS
NOT A LAW ENFORCEMENT OFFICER.

36:49.990 --> 36:53.950
-OVERRULED, IT WAS WITHIN
HER JURISDICTION TO TAKE

36:54.081 --> 36:55.430
WHATEVER ACTION
SHE DEEMED APPROPRIATE.

36:55.561 --> 36:59.042
-IT'S NOT SURPRISING
GIVEN YOUR LAX ATTITUDE.

36:59.173 --> 37:01.044
YOU FAILED TO REMEMBER
THAT THOMAS O'HARA

37:01.175 --> 37:02.872
WAS ON BOARD THE
BOAT THAT NIGHT.

37:03.003 --> 37:04.918
-I DIDN'T SEE HIM
THAT NIGHT.

37:06.485 --> 37:08.138
-AND THAT'S WHY
HE DIED, ISN'T IT?

37:08.269 --> 37:09.183
-STEVE: OBJECTION.

37:09.314 --> 37:10.663
-SUSTAINED.

37:11.664 --> 37:12.708
-NO FURTHER QUESTIONS.

37:16.538 --> 37:19.106
-YOUR HONOR, AT THIS
TIME I WOULD LIKE TO MOVE

37:19.237 --> 37:20.629
THE PROCEEDINGS OUT
INTO THE MARINA.

37:22.283 --> 37:23.850
-ARE THERE ANY OBJECTIONS?

37:23.980 --> 37:26.287
-I THINK WE COULD ALL
USE A BREATH OF FRESH AIR.

37:26.418 --> 37:29.508
[SOMBER MUSIC]

37:35.470 --> 37:37.733
-WHEN THE POLICE
INTERVIEWED THE SURVIVORS,

37:37.864 --> 37:39.735
THE BOYS SAID THAT COWBOY
WAS PASSED OUT ON THE DECK

37:39.866 --> 37:40.867
OF THE BOAT, WAS THAT CORRECT?

37:40.997 --> 37:42.434
-YES.

37:42.564 --> 37:44.000
-SO THERE IS NO WAY
YOU COULD'VE SEEN HIM

37:44.131 --> 37:45.611
OR EVEN KNOWN HE
WAS ON THAT BOAT.

37:45.741 --> 37:47.177
-THAT'S RIGHT.
-OBJECTION, YOUR HONOR.

37:47.308 --> 37:49.223
THAT HASN'T BEEN ESTABLISHED AS FACT.

37:49.354 --> 37:51.921
-YOUR HONOR, I INTEND
TO ESTABLISH THAT HERE NOW.

37:52.052 --> 37:53.619
-PLEASE, CONTINUE.

37:53.749 --> 37:57.318
-THIS IS WHERE CAROLINE
WAS DOCKED WHEN SHE OBSERVED

37:57.449 --> 37:59.146
THE BOYS HEADED OUT THE CHANNEL.

37:59.277 --> 38:02.236
WHAT YOU'RE SEEING HERE IS
EXACTLY WHAT SHE SAW THAT NIGHT.

38:03.063 --> 38:05.935
THAT BOAT IS THE
SAME MAKE AND MODEL

38:06.066 --> 38:07.807
AS THE ONE THAT
CAUGHT FIRE AND BURNT.

38:09.243 --> 38:12.246
MRS. O'HARA, HOW
MANY BOYS DO YOU SEE?

38:12.377 --> 38:15.249
-ROSE, YOU DON'T HAVE
TO ANSWER THAT QUESTION.

38:20.515 --> 38:21.995
-I SEE FOUR.

38:22.865 --> 38:24.214
-CHRIS?

38:33.006 --> 38:35.008
[BOYS SHOUTING]

38:35.138 --> 38:37.532
-HEY, GUYS, WHY DON'T
YOU CALL IT A DAY, HUH?

38:37.663 --> 38:39.882
[BOYS SHOUTING]

38:45.801 --> 38:48.238
-AS YOU CAN SEE WITH YOUR
OWN EYES, MRS. O'HARA,

38:48.369 --> 38:51.894
CAROLINE HOLDEN COULD NOT
HAVE KNOWN THAT YOUR SON

38:52.460 --> 38:54.157
WAS PASSED OUT ON THE
DECK OF THAT BOAT.

38:54.288 --> 38:57.639
TO HOLD HER LIABLE FOR
HIS DEATH WOULD BE WRONG.

39:04.733 --> 39:05.952
-MAN:
TWO WEEKS AND...

39:06.082 --> 39:07.345
-OKAY.

39:07.475 --> 39:09.695
-JUDGE: SORRY.
-OKAY, THANK YOU.

39:10.652 --> 39:11.784
BYE.

39:15.831 --> 39:18.704
-WELL, THAT'S IT, THE
ARBITRATOR WILL HAVE A WRITTEN

39:18.834 --> 39:20.401
DECISION IN ABOUT TWO WEEKS.

39:20.532 --> 39:21.924
-TWO WEEKS?

39:22.055 --> 39:23.273
YOU MEAN I HAVE
TO HAVE THIS THING HANGING

39:23.404 --> 39:24.927
OVER MY HEAD FOR
ANOTHER TWO WEEKS?

39:25.058 --> 39:27.843
-WHAT CAN I SAY? THE WHEELS
OF JUSTICE TURN SLOWLY.

39:27.974 --> 39:30.019
-THAT WAS A BRILLIANT
TACTICAL MANEUVER

39:30.150 --> 39:31.325
GETTING EVERYONE
ON THIS SCARAB.

39:31.456 --> 39:33.022
WELL DONE, COUNCILOR.

39:33.153 --> 39:35.373
-THANK YOU, CAPTAIN,
BUT LET'S HOLD THE APPLAUSE

39:35.503 --> 39:37.113
UNTIL WE SEE HOW
EFFECTIVE IT WAS.

39:40.639 --> 39:41.727
-I...

39:42.989 --> 39:47.036
I JUST WANTED
TO TELL YOU THAT I,

39:47.167 --> 39:51.040
I'VE DECIDED
TO DROP MY LAWSUIT.

39:51.171 --> 39:53.521
-ROSE, I STRONGLY ADVISE
YOU AGAINST DOING THAT.

39:53.652 --> 39:56.655
-YOU WERE THE ONE WHO
PUSHED ME INTO THIS.

39:59.309 --> 40:01.573
I NEVER WANTED
TO SUE ANYONE.

40:01.703 --> 40:04.445
I DON'T CARE
ABOUT THE MONEY.

40:06.621 --> 40:07.970
I GUESS I...

40:09.711 --> 40:11.321
I NEEDED TO BLAME SOMEONE.

40:11.452 --> 40:16.675
MAYBE I WAS BLINDED
BY MY ANGER, OR I DON'T KNOW,

40:16.805 --> 40:18.198
I DON'T KNOW.

40:18.328 --> 40:20.896
I'M SORRY I PUT YOU
THROUGH THIS ORDEAL.

40:21.027 --> 40:24.465
-MRS. O'HARA,
IT'S OKAY, AND I DON'T KNOW

40:24.596 --> 40:25.901
IF THIS IS GOING TO MAKE
YOU FEEL ANY BETTER,

40:27.076 --> 40:29.905
BUT NOT A DAY HAS GONE
BY SINCE YOUR SON'S DEATH

40:30.036 --> 40:31.777
THAT I HAVEN'T
THOUGHT ABOUT HIM.

40:31.907 --> 40:34.519
AND NOTHING THAT WAS SAID TODAY
WILL EVER, EVER CHANGE THAT.

40:36.042 --> 40:37.304
HE'LL ALWAYS BE ON MY MIND.

40:40.568 --> 40:43.571
[TRIUMPHANT MUSIC]

40:55.104 --> 40:57.063
[LAUGHING]

41:13.601 --> 41:17.823
[CLOSING THEME PLAYING]
